OL,3,CThe Windermere Children return to
OL,4,Cwhere they found sanctuary after WW2
OL,6,FBelan Millan, who was three years old
OL,7,Fwhen she arrived in England, says no
OL,8,Fone told them that "we'd been
OL,9,Fliberated".
OL,11,FShe said: "I think that made it more
OL,12,Fdifficult for us because nobody had
OL,13,Ftold us. Gradually, we settled down
OL,14,Fand we understood that we were going
OL,15,Fto be given proper food to eat, but we
OL,16,Fhad no explanations. We'd never been
OL,17,Fin a family situation. We grew up in
OL,18,Fthe camp; we were there for two years,
OL,19,Fjust the six of us.
OL,1,W{$~k4{$k4~sjw=                 G2/6
