OL,3,CThe Windermere Children return to
OL,4,Cwhere they found sanctuary after WW2
OL,6,FThe service included a walk-through of
OL,7,Fthe areas where survivors lived during
OL,8,Ftheir time in Cumbria.
OL,10,FDavid Shannon attended the event to
OL,11,Fpay respects to his uncle and aunt,
OL,12,Ftwo of the survivors who temporarily
OL,13,Frelocated to the Lake District.
OL,15,FHe said: "It is important to me
OL,16,Fbecause this is where their journey
OL,17,Fstarted for the rest of their lives.
OL,18,FThey had long, successful lives -
OL,19,Fhappy lives. It's a place that's very
OL,20,Fspecial. I like to come here and think
OL,21,Fabout all the survivors.
