OL,3,CThe Windermere Children return to
OL,4,Cwhere they found sanctuary after WW2
OL,6,F"Coming here was a place of safety. I
OL,7,Fremember asking my aunt five years
OL,8,Fago, before I came here, 'What did
OL,9,FWindermere mean to you?'
OL,11,F"She talked about the beauty, the
OL,12,Fflowers, she talked about the white
OL,13,Fbread... she never had white bread,
OL,14,Fshe said it was like cake. She had
OL,15,Fwhite bread with jam."
